"title": "6670: grace, and Holy Spirit",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6670",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The Holy Spirit is both an expression of God's grace and the means by which it is experienced.</p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit is himself a gracious gift of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:5-Acts6:8\">ACT 6:5–6:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:4-Titus3:7\">TIT 3:4–3:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:24\">1JN 3:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:21-John20:22\">JHN 20:21–20:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:32\">ACT 5:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:15-Acts11:17\">ACT 11:15–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:6-Acts15:8\">ACT 15:6–15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:12\">1CO 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14\">GAL 3:14</a></p>\n<h3>Through the Holy Spirit God brings believers out of slavery and into his family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15-Rom8:16\">ROM 8:15–8:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:6–4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:17-Eph2:18\">EPH 2:17–2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Through the Holy Spirit God equips believers to serve him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:7\">1CO 12:4–12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37-John7:39\">JHN 7:37–7:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:31\">ACT 4:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:5\">ROM 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:5\">GAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit in God's gracious work of redemption</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:2\">ROM 8:1–8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:4-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:13\">1CO 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:4-1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:4–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:12\">1PE 1:12</a></p>\n<h2>The Holy Spirit in God's gracious work of sanctifying and sustaining his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:17–3:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:31\">ACT 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26-Rom8:27\">ROM 8:26–8:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17-Rom14:18\">ROM 14:17–14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:13\">ROM 15:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:4-Gal5:5\">GAL 5:4–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:8\">GAL 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:22\">EPH 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:16-Eph3:20\">EPH 3:16–3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:18-Phil1:19\">PHP 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:29\">HEB 10:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4-Jas4:6\">JAS 4:4–4:6</a></p>",
